review_title: Day in the Life of a Package Handler
job_title: Package Handler in Fort Myers, FL
pros:
FedEx hires all backgrounds and races. If you are looking to start your first job, Fed Ex will hire you, given that you meet the physical qualifications for the job.

Work-life balance at FedEx Ground is good if you are an early riser. Expect to be going to bed by 7pm the latest, as you will be waking up at 2am to be there from 3am working till 8am. Bring a large bottle of water with you, as you will be working hard the entire time.

Pay and benefits for FedEx Ground (and privately owned) is probably the worst out of all the Fed Ex companies. If you are looking for pay and benefits, do not apply at a privately owned Fed Ex site. Also, apply for a Driver position instead.

In terms of job security at FedEx Ground, ‘package handler’ is an essential job. It’s also your foot in the door as to how shipping companies work. If you can handle your schedule changing constantly, your job is secure.
cons:
Turnover rate is high. Burnout rate is high.

Multiple call-offs per day.

No PTO. 

Medical benefits are only for those in it for the long haul. I worked during the pandemic and did not receive Covid pay. However, I was only there for a few months.

If trucks are late, or if routes change, expect your shift to end around noon. Oh, and you will not receive overtime.

While FedEx has diversity, not all can assist you in lifting heavy packages. Expect to pick up packages as heavy as 100 lbs by yourself sometimes.

 Calling out is considered by management as a no/call no/show. Provide a dr note to manager if you need to call out.

review_title: Day in the Life of a Package Handler
job_title: Package Handler in Fort Myers, FL
pros:
FedEx hires all backgrounds and races. If you are looking to start your first job, Fed Ex will hire you, given that you meet the physical qualifications for the job.

Work-life balance at FedEx Ground is good if you are an early riser. Expect to be going to bed by 7pm the latest, as you will be waking up at 2am to be there from 3am working till 8am. Bring a large bottle of water with you, as you will be working hard the entire time.

Pay and benefits for FedEx Ground (and privately owned) is probably the worst out of all the Fed Ex companies. If you are looking for pay and benefits, do not apply at a privately owned Fed Ex site. Also, apply for a Driver position instead.

In terms of job security at FedEx Ground, ‘package handler’ is an essential job. It’s also your foot in the door as to how shipping companies work. If you can handle your schedule changing constantly, your job is secure.
cons:
Turnover rate is high. Burnout rate is high.

Multiple call-offs per day.

No PTO. 

Medical benefits are only for those in it for the long haul. I worked during the pandemic and did not receive Covid pay. However, I was only there for a few months.

If trucks are late, or if routes change, expect your shift to end around noon. Oh, and you will not receive overtime.

While FedEx has diversity, not all can assist you in lifting heavy packages. Expect to pick up packages as heavy as 100 lbs by yourself sometimes.

 Calling out is considered by management as a no/call no/show. Provide a dr note to manager if you need to call out.
